Temperatures fell below freezing on Friday morning in many parts of the Eastern Cape interior, according to the Port Elizabeth office of the South African Weather Service. " This morning showed the first REAL sign of winter," said Garth Sampson, Client Liaison Officer for the Eastern Cape at the South African Weather Service. "At 6 am this morning the mercury dropped to 1.4 C. It is the coldest this year and the coldest since 3 July last year (2016)"Also is the joint coldest day in June since 2013 when the mercury dropped to 1.1 C."Minimum temperaturesOtherAccording to the SA Weather Service website, s evere frost is also expected in places in the northern interior of the Eastern Cape on Friday.